Enum ModelSerializer.WriteDisposition

    ModelSerializer<Model extends com.google.protobuf.Message,​Output>
    public static enum ModelSerializer.WriteDisposition
extends java.lang.Enum<ModelSerializer.WriteDisposition>
    Describes available write dispositions, each of which presents a strategy that governs how an individual write operation is handled with regard to underlying storage. Each option is explained in its own documentation.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • BLIND

        public static final ModelSerializer.WriteDisposition BLIND
        Blind writes. Just applies the write without regard to side effects.

      • CREATE

        public static final ModelSerializer.WriteDisposition CREATE
        Create-style writes. Guarantees the object does not exist before writing.

      • UPDATE

        public static final ModelSerializer.WriteDisposition UPDATE
        Update-style writes. Guarantees the object does exist before writing.
